'''Mariya Didi''' (born August 18, 1962) is a [[Maldivians|Maldivian]] barrister and politician currently serving as the Minister of Defense of the Maldives.<ref name=":0" /> After being the campaign manager<ref>{{Cite web |title=Minister Mariya appointed as Pres Solih's campaign spokesperson |url=https://avas.mv/en/126752 |access-date=2023-03-10 |website=avas.mv |language=en}}</ref> for president [[Ibrahim Mohamed Solih]] during the 2018 elections, she was appointed the nation’s first-ever female Minister of Defence.<ref name=":0" />
Mariya received her Bachelor’s degree in Law and Master’s degree in Law from the [[Aberystwyth University|University of Aberystwyth]], Wales, United Kingdom<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=MNDF |url=https://mndf.gov.mv/mndf/en/minister-of-defence.php |access-date=2023-03-10 |website=mndf.gov.mv}}</ref> and became the first woman lawyer in the Maldives.
Mariya Didi, in her capacity as Minister of Defence, oversees a total of 8 critical institutions, namely Maldives National Defence Force (MNDF), National Counter Terrorism Center (NCTC), National Disaster Management Authority (NDMA), Maldives Customs Service, Maldives Immigration, Aviation Security Command (AVSECOM), Anti-Trafficking in Persons (Anti-TIP) Office and Maldives Hydrographic Service{{Citation needed|date=March 2023}}.
