'''Mariya Didi''' ([[Maldivian language|Maldivian]]:މާރިޔާ ދީދީ''';''' born August 18, 1962) is a [[Maldivians|Maldivian]] barrister and politician currently serving as the Minister of Defense of the Maldives.<ref name=":0" /> After being the campaign manager<ref>{{Cite web |title=Minister Mariya appointed as Pres Solih's campaign spokesperson |url=https://avas.mv/en/126752 |access-date=2023-03-10 |website=avas.mv |language=en}}</ref> for president [[Ibrahim Mohamed Solih]] during the 2018 elections, she was appointed the nation’s first-ever female Minister of Defence.<ref name=":0" />
